must have in order to be signified by the phonetic material of a name, verb or assertive sentence, and why noêmata can fulfil those logical conditions. Finally, I elucidate the significans-significatum relation without making use of the modern semantic triangle. This approach is consonant with Aristotle’s methodology and breaks new ground by exploring the connection between the linguistic and psychological aspects of Aristotle’s theory of signification.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aGreek literaturexHistory and criticism. 0aPsychology in literature. 0aSignification (Logic) in literature. 4aAristoteles. 4aDe Interpretatione. 4aPsychologie. 4aSinn. 4aSprache. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aAristotle.  aDe Interpretatione.  aLanguage.  aPsychology.  aSignification.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Classics and Near East Studies 2000-2014 (EN)z978311062109908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Classics and Near East Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110636178oZDB-23-GCN08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2012z9783110288995oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE CLASSICAL STUDIES 2012z9783110293838oZDB-23-DGD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET ALTERTUM 2012z9783110288964oZDB-23-DGD0 cprintz978311028765340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311028987940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110289879423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110289879/original  a978-3-11-023857-0  DGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1c2000d2014  a978-3-11-062109-9  DGBA Backli